Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.68,0:01:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Newscaster] Although rioting in Mantle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.28,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is finally under control,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it feel to know that the majority
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of those involved were your supporters?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:01:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't condone rioting,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.62,0:02:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when our\Ncity is being denied aid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.82,0:02:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for the hardships we've\Nalready had to go through,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jacques Schnee's\Nlatest stunt is holding
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.42,0:02:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the city hostage for\Nhis own political gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.24,0:02:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I understand their anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.29,0:02:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but ask that they show\Nit not in the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the polls today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah, ah!\N(ball banging)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah!\N(weapon buzzing)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.69,0:02:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nice, your recovery is getting faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.54,0:03:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] Have you always\Nbeen able to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.83,0:03:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- (panting) I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.33,0:03:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't normally think\Nit through that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- You guys are evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.86,0:03:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still don't even have my Semblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.18,0:03:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Well, I bet we'll\Nall be jealous when you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.75,0:03:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Clover wasn't kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.40,0:03:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really giving this your all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, we have to with\Nthe way things are going.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.16,0:03:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're not going well, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.94,0:03:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Better Robyn then Jacques Schnee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Oh, I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, this election\Ndoesn't bode well
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.99,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for our stability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- It could be a chance to work with Robyn
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.98,0:03:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and get Mantle on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- The likelihood of that working --
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] She's right,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to do something\Nabout Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.60,0:03:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could get Robin to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.63,0:03:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- I bet if you opened up\Nto her she'd understand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're being framed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.80,0:03:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- (sighs) Perhaps,\Nbut it will only work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.82,0:03:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if she's open too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.74,0:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- I take it your here for\Nnew mission assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:03:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:03:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The General and I want\Nyou to take the rest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:04:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the day to recuperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're giving us a night off?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ordering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,After tonight's election,\Nwe'll be waking up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.44,0:04:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to a very different Atlas tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.62,0:04:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you rested and ready\Nfor whatever that may bring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Newscaster] We still\Nhave hours ahead of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.45,0:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but as votes come in, it\Nlooks more and more certain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.68,0:04:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that Robyn Hill will fill\Nthe open council seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.60,0:04:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- There's no way my\Nfather could've thought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.13,0:04:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,layoffs would do anything but hurt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.40,0:04:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So why announce this the\Nday before the election?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just seems like a power\Nplay that backfired to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.23,0:04:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't matter in a few hours though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where are you guys going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Team FNKI invited us out dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yang and I thought it would be good
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.70,0:04:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to get our minds off the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought you said\NTeam FNKI was annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's the best part about dance clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(whispers) I can't hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.28,0:04:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I still can't believe\Nyou're going to that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.62,0:04:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just because Ironwood dislikes Robyn
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.51,0:04:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean we all have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.37,0:05:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,From where I'm standing, both\Nof them seem to be trying
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.12,0:05:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,their best to help Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As to who's doing a better job...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.06,0:05:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- (sighs) But a victory party?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Invite's still open if you want in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.84,0:05:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Penny's gonna be working security.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh my gosh, no. You\Ngotta do it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.51,0:05:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's what I'm doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.86,0:05:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, Oscar and I are hitting the\Nmovies if anyone wants --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yup!\N- Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.28,0:05:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ren] I understand Weiss' point though,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a victory party does\Nseem a bit premature.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Aw, let them have one sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.57,0:05:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Probably the last sure thing\Nbefore Amity Tower goes up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.88,0:05:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone learns about...\Nwhat we're fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.08,0:05:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- We spent so much time worrying
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,about how Ironwood will\Nreact to the truth about her,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but have any of us considered
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how we're even going to beat her\Nif we manage to work past that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.36,0:05:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] Jinn said she can't be beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.30,0:05:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] She told Oz that he couldn't destroy her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.36,0:05:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- But maybe someone else could?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- We should be training right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.08,0:06:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- We've trained enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Take some time to --
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- We don't have time!
